  </a>
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
  Wings
</h3>
<p>
  Wing location is extracted from a prisoner’s full cell location in the general prison population table.
</p>
<p>
  Any analysis at wing level checks the relevant date and pulls the location assigned to the prisoner at that time.
  This leads to a small number of non-standard locations such as hospital (HOSP), cell swap (CSWAP), reception (RECP) for example that might not reflect the prisoner’s true wing location at that time.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
  Regional benchmark groups
</h3>
<p>
  The PGD region grouping is an administrative grouping, on which prisons are under a Prison Group Director.
  The groupings are extracted from a workbook maintained and developed by HMPPS.
</p>
