</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
  Source data
</h3>
<p>
  The data used to populate the charts in the service comes from the Ministry of Justice Analytical Platform (MoJAP) which extracts information from Prison NOMIS daily and mirrors the NOMIS database to within 24 hours.
  It is important to remember that all data in NOMIS is only as accurate or timely as the NOMIS application users who enter the data.
</p>
<p>
  The tables used to extract information from this service are:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
  <li>
    nomis_dn_pp.prisons – used to extract active prisons
  </li>
  <li>
    Prison lookup list.xlsx – from ‘HMPPS Performance Team’ to get PGD Region for each prison.
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_sens.offender_case_notes – used to extract behaviour entries
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_ao.core – used to extract core information about prisoners (date, prison, full location for wing, age, gender)
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_ao.identifiers – used to extract prisoner IDs
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_ao.regimes – used to extract the prisoners incentive level
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_ao.profiles – used to extract prisoner characteristics (ethnicity, religion, faith and belief)
  </li>
  <li>
    nomis_sens.offender_profile_details – used to extract more sensitive, protected prisoner characteristics (sexual orientation and disability)
  </li>
</ul>
